
                                  The Cycon
                                   Odyssey

(Introduction:) You awaken and everything is blurry. You sit up, rub your 
eyes and notice that you somehow have arrived in the middle of a beach. Your 
clothes are torn, and your throat is a little sore. Slowly you get up to your 
feet and look around. This is the start of a long and wonderful journey. You 
must use logic, as well as wits and courage. You don't know how you got here, 
but maybe you can get home.`
001"You are standing on a large beachfront. In front of you lies a huge forest 
with a wide assortment of trees, including a few abnormally large ones. You 
notice that the western portion of this island is made up of a series of 
cliffs and rocky terrain."
B"on a beachfront."
D"You can see a shady spot to under a tree the NorthWest, a forest starts to 
the NorthEast, and the beach extends both SouthWest and SouthEast. There is 
also a path that leads into the forest to the North."`
002"From where you are standing, there are waves crashing to the south, and you 
can see something being pushed up and down the beach by waves just northeast 
of here."
B"on a beach."
I"You can see the beginning of a forest to the North, and the beach extends 
both NorthEast and NorthWest."`
003"There is a very large oak tree here, one of the largest in the forest. 
One of its lower branches is within your reach, although there is no reason 
for you to climb it."
B"at the base of a large oak."
I"You think you hear something rustling in the leaves on the North side of 
the tree. It sounds like a small squirrel or rabbit. Towards the East you can 
see the sun casting shadows on the ground, and the beach runs SouthWest and 
SouthEast of here."`
004"You have come to the edge of the beach, and the abruptness of it's ending 
is due to the fact that there is an extremely large cliff here. It is much 
too steep for you to climb up, but maybe coming down would be a bit 
easier..."
B"at the bottom of a cliff."
I"Because of the cliff, you can only go NorthEast along the coastline, or 
head North towards a shady spot."`
005"The many limbs of the trees that hang far above you easily block out
the sun and make the sand more comfortable, since it is less hot."
B"in a shady spot."
I"The beach ends to the South and continues to the SouthEast. There is a huge 
oak tree to the East, and it looks as though you can climb up an old rock 
slide just West of here."`
006"The ocean's waves are crashing far below you, and your loose footing here 
makes you nervous. You'd like to leave this area as soon as possible."
B"halfway up a cliff."
I"You can either move along the cliff to the North, or slide Downwards to the 
beach below."`
007"Apparently there once was a rock-slide here some time ago, making for 
loose footing. It is impossible to continue up the cliff from this direction."
B"on top of a rockslide."
I"You have the choice of either working your way along the edge of the 
rockslide Southward, or simply sliding East and down to the shady spot
below."`
008"You are at the start of a long path, which winds through the forest that 
now surrounds you on both sides."
B"at the start of a path."
I"You can either go South to the beach, or follow the path to the North."`
009" There is a piece of wreckage being pushed up and down the beach by the 
waves here. At first you thought it was just driftwood, but after closer 
look, you recognize it as once being something of your own, and you remember 
it had something to do with your getting here...but you can remember no more."
B"on the beach."
"The beach continues SouthWest and NorthEast, and there is a large tree to 
the NorthWest."`
010"The woods on either side of the path are very close together and almost 
no light can get through."
B"on a path."
I"Rather than wander away, you'd prefer to stay on the path; therefore you 
can go either North or South."`
011"As you look toward the South, your eyes widen, and your mouth gapes, for 
before you stands a huge temple that was built into the rockface behind it!"
B"at the bottom of a temple."
I"Your choices are either going Up the steps to the top of the temple, East 
to a river bank, or West to the start of a rope bridge."`
012"It is very dark here, since most of the light is blocked out by the 
trees."
B"surrounded by trees."
I"The only direction to go is East, where there is more light."`
013"The path forks here, in three directions."
B"in front of a fork in the road."
I"You can either head West towards the largest tree in the forest, North to 
where the path forks again, or follow the path to the East or South."`
014"You are now behind the oak tree, and whatever made
that noise is gone. Instead, someone has left behind a rope that goes (-where
else-) up!"
B"behind the large oak tree."
I"You can either go up the rope, or South to the other side of the tree. "`
015"You are standing on one of the lower branches of the tree. There is no 
way to go back, so you have to climb down."
B"on a low branch."
I"You may only climb Down to a shady cove."`
016"A huge tree blocks the rest of the path, so you can't continue in this 
direction. You do however, notice a large platform far up above you, in the
trees. By no means can you get to it from here, but there has to be a way..."
B"at the base of a huge tree."
I"You may only go East."`
017"You are on a path."
B"on a path."
I"The path ends to the North, continues to the NorthWest, and there is an 
open field to the East."`
018"When you peer over the edge of the platform, you immediately notice just 
how high up you really are, well over 40 feet. There is not much to do here,
so you might as well continue your journey."
B"on a platform."
I"You can probably jump to (and hope to reach in time) either of the branches 
that are both North and South of here."`
019"This long and wide branch extends far out from the tree. There is also a 
vine hanging here which looks sturdy enough to hold your weight."
B"on a large branch."
I"You can climb Down the tree, follow the limb off to the West, where it 
hangs over a wall, or swing on the vine over to a platform, just South of 
here."`
020"You are near the end of the beach."
B"on a beach."
I"The beach extends both South and SouthWest, and ends off to the East."`
021"The road forks here, in two directions."
B"at a fork in the road."
I"You can go along the trail to the West, South, or SouthEast."`
022"You are on the north side of the huge tree, where there an arrow is 
lodged into its trunk so far that you cannot possibly budge it."
B"behind the huge tree."
I"You may go East to a fork in the road, or North towards a huge boulder."`
023"You are in an open field."
B"in an open field."
I"Because of the trees, you can only go North or West, along a winding path."`
024"You have come to the end of the path, where it becomes surrounded by 
groups of trees huddled very close together. Just north of the trees you can
see a few of the many huge cliffs and other mountainous regions that make up 
the western and northern portions of the island."
B"at the end of the path."
I"You have to go back to the South."`
025"The field begins to break down into sand, and you can see a lagoon off 
in the distance."
B"within sight of a lagoon."
I"There is a sandbank to the North, the southern shore of a lagoon to the 
NorthEast, and a field to the South."`
026"You make it onto one of the farther limbs of the tree. Since the wind 
keeps shaking the end of the beach, you'd like to continue on your journey 
just as soon as possible."
B"on a far limb."
I"You can go back to the North, or climb Down to a lower branch."`
027"You caught the limb and are now swinging back and forth. The friction is 
starting to hurt your bare hands, so you'd like to move on."
B"swinging on a branch."
I"You can try to swing over, release and try to land in either the massive 
bird's nest south of you, or onto a platform just North of here."`
028"You are now standing in the middle of huge nest that is nuzzled in the 
place where this branch meets the trunk of the tree."
B"in a huge nest."
I"You can jump and grab for either of the limbs just North and South of 
here."`
029"You are at the southern shore of a lagoon that's glimmering in the 
sunlight. Far ahead lies a rope bridge that crosses it."
B"south of a lagoon."
I"You can go North to the edge of the water, West towards a sandbank, or 
SouthWest towards a field."`
030"You are standing on a sandbank which is home to many exotic species of 
flora."
B"on a sandbank."
I"You can head North to the southwestern bank of the lagoon, East to the 
it's southern bank, South towards a field, or West towards one of this 
island's many cliffs."`
031"There is a wide assortment of seashells here, ranging from large conches, 
to small muscles and clams."
B"standing admist many seashells."
I"Apparently, you can only go North along the beach."` 
032"You have come to the edge of the cliff, and are enjoying a spectacular 
view of your surroundings."
B"at the edge of the cliff."
I"You can probably climb Down along the cliff, but you won't be able to get 
back up. You also may go North or SouthWest."`
033"The tree has a large knothole in it here, probably even large enough for 
you to crawl into. The hole leads downward through the trunk, which you now 
realize has been hollowed out. Also, there is a branch with a rope tied to it
that is within your reach."
B"at the entrance to the tree."
I"You can go East and down through the hollow trunk, or climb Down the rope 
hanging from the branch to where you think you can hear something rustling 
in the leaves."`
034"You are at the bottom of the large hollow tree, which is apparently just 
camouflage for a series of underground tunnels. Light is pouring in through
an enlarged knothole above you."
B"inside a large hollow tree."
I"You can follow this tunnel to the East, or climb Up through the tree to the 
wide knothole."`
035"You have come to the end of the beach, so you'll have to go back the way 
you came."
B"at the end of the beach."
I"You can only go back East."`
036"You are on an overpass that reaches out over the beaches below. You are 
enjoying the view, but the ground isn't very stable."
B"on an overpass."
I"You may go South to the edge of the cliff, or SouthWest towards a pathway 
up the volcano."`
037"You are on a pathway that leads up a volcano that seems to have erupted 
recently."
B"on a pathway up the volcano."
I"You can go Up the volcano towards a small dugout, West where there is more 
hardened lava, East to an overpass, or down the path to the South."`
038"From where you now stand, you face north towards a huge volcano, looming 
in the distance. Behind you the rockface begins to drop off towards the 
crashing sea below."
B"south of a looming volcano."
I"You can head North up a path to the top of the volcano, or follow the cliff 
to the SouthWest or NorthEast."`
039"This area is mostly covered with hardened lava, from a recent eruption."
B"walking on hardened lava."
I"You may go East towards a pathway that leads up the volcano, West to the 
southwestern tip of the island, or South towards an ocean viewpoint."`
040"Your current position allows you to gaze out across the ocean, and relish 
the magnificent view."
B"at an ocean viewpoint."
I"You can go North toward some hardened lava, NorthEast to the southwestern 
tip of the island, or NorthEast towards a steep drop-off point."`
041"You are on top of a wide wall, struggling to keep your balance."
B"on top of a wall."
I"You can go North where to where the wall is higher up off the ground, West 
along the wall, or climb up onto a branch that hangs over the wall to the 
East."`
042"You have come across an area that looks as though someone has recently 
camped here."
B"at a campsite."
I"You may only go back East, to the edge of the cliff."`
043"You are standing on a very weak portion of the wall."
B"on a weak part of a wall."
I"You can go East to the far end of the wall, West to the western edge of 
the wall, or jump Down towards the pasture below."`
044"You are standing at the water's edge. Strangly, the lagoon would appear 
to be salt-water, so you can't drink it. However, what may be of more 
importance, any sort of sea-creature could be lying within the water's murky 
depths."
B"at the edge of the water."
I"You could go Down into the water (if you had something that would allow you 
to breathe underwater), West to the southwest end of the lagoon, South to the 
beginning of the sand, or swim North and under the bridge towards a coral 
reef on the other side."`
045"You are standing next to a large cliff, which blocks all passages to the 
north."
B"next to a large cliff."
I"You can go either East to a sandbank at the edge of a lagoon, or West 
towards a large boulder."`
046"A large passageway has been cut sheer through the cliffs on either side 
of you. Whoever made the passageway, however, probably didn't want anyone 
going through, because they also left a large boulder here to block the path."
B"in front of a passageway through the cliffs."
I"You can go East along the cliff, South behind a huge tree, or North (once 
you find a way to remove that boulder)."`
047"This area is where the deliberate presence of the tunnel becomes very 
obvious. The roots of the tree surrounds you, almost as if they were meant to 
go around the tunnel in the first place. The most interesting thing, however,
is that the tunnel itself does not seem to have been dug with tools, but the 
dirt simply pushed aside with a great deal of force."
B"surrounded by roots."
I"You can crawl to the North where the tunnel forks, or West towards the 
hololwed trunk of a large tree."`
048"You are traveling along a path that leads upwards."
B"on a path leading upwards."
I"The path splits to the East and West."`
049"You are on the edge of a small overhang. There is something down there, 
but you can neither see it, nor hear anything."
B"on a ledge."
I"You could probably jump Down below without breaking any bones, but there is 
absolutely no possible way to get back up here. You can also head back East."`
050"After you place your lips around the small end of the conch, you close 
your eyes and blow. You think that you can hear something and your eyelids 
snap open. Before you stands a huge winged unicorn. It doesn't look 
frightened, so you walk over, pet its long mane, and climb up onto its back.  
     You are now riding on the back of a beautiful winged unicorn. It reminds
you of the mythological creature 'Pegasus'. You can see most of the island 
from up here. Apparently the western part of the island drops off about 100 
feet or so, and most of the plant life is on the lower and eastern half. You 
can see a lagoon on the northeastern part of the island, and a volcano on the 
southwestern portion.                                                         
     The unicorn is descending now.(Please return your seats to an upright 
position.)"
B"on the back of a winged unicorn."
I" "`
051"The path ends here, so you'll have to head back."
B"facing an unclimbable hill."
I"You can only go back to the East."`
052"It feels as though this area has a magical aura all around it. The sun's 
rays of light shining down into the water seem to cause everything to 
sparkle. It's a shame that the saltwater hurts your eyes so much."
B"underwater."
I"You can barely make out what appears to be an underwater cave, far below 
you. You can swim Down and into it, North towards a coral reef, or up to the 
edge of the water."`
053"You have come across a large hole where the ground has caved in. It looks 
as though this was once a trap made to catch unsuspecting animals. A 
makeshift ladder leads into the depths of the pit."
B"in front of a pitfall."
I"You can climb Down the ladder, and into the pit, or go North to one of the 
banks of the lagoon."`
054"As you look around you notice that this was indeed once a trap to catch 
animals. It looks like it was used recently, but there is no immediate 
evidence of what was caught."
B"in a pit."
I"You may only climb back Up the ladder."`
055"This side of the lagoon is seems less tranquil than the opposite bank. 
There is less plant-life here and it is much more quiet. You would prefer to 
move on as soon as possible."
B"on the other side of the bridge that crosses the lagoon."
I"You can go West across the bridge, North to the east shore of the lagoon, 
South towards a pit, or East towards a large patch of sand, which seems 
out-of-place in its forest surroundings."`
056"You are in the middle of a long rope bridge that crosses the lagoon. You 
stare down at the water, to try to see what's at the bottom, but its too 
murky and there is too much reflection from the sun for you to be able to see
much of anything."
B"in the middle of a long rope bridge."
I"The bridge extends both East and West across the lagoon. You could also 
dive Down into the waters of the lagoon below you."`
057"You are at the southwest bank of the lagoon. A path winds along the cliff 
to the East. You can also hear a river that is not too far from here."
B"at the southwest bank of the lagoon."
I"You can go North or South alongside of the cliff, or East to the edge of 
the water."`
058"Walking side-by-side along the cliff, you continue through the patch of 
sand. You're almost positive that you can hear a river nearby."
B"west of the lagoon."
I"You can go South to the southwest bank of the lagoon, or North towards a 
bridge that crosses the middle of the lagoon."`
059"You are standing next to a long rope bridge that spans the width of the 
lagoon. It appears to be the only way across the lagoon, but at least you're 
sure that it is more than strong enough to hold your weight."
B"standing next to the rope bridge." 
I"You can go North to the western shore, cross the bridge by going East, or 
walk alongside fo the cliff to the South. "`
060"You are on the east shore of the lagoon. To the north and east of you are 
some of those patches of sand. You can't go west because of a coral reef 
which is blocking your path." 
B"on the east shore of the lagoon."
I"You only may go South to the rope bridge, or East and find out what that 
sand doing there."`
061"As you glance over your shoulder, you notice that the cliffs start 
bending around to the west, allowing you to head over towards a river that 
has eroded a small passage way through the rockface."
B"on the west shore of the lagoon."
I"You can head West to where a group of rocks would allow you to cross the 
river, North to a small sand dune, or South to the rope bridge that crosses 
the lagoon."`
062"You've come across a large coral reef which blocks your passage forward. 
It is covered by a wide assortment of seaweed and crushed shells. The lagoon 
was probably a part of the ocean at one time, which would explain the 
saltwater."
B"treading water in front of a coral reef."
I"You can only swim over to the South because the coral reef blocks further 
passage."`
063"The sand in this area has piled up to create a small dune. The dune 
doesn't look like it was formed naturally, and a closer look confirms this 
because you notice that a tunnel with carved stone steps going downward have 
been built into the other side of the sand dune."
B"standing on a small sand dune."
I"You can go North to the other side of the dune, West toward a river, East 
to the north shore of the lagoon, or South to it's west shore."`
064"The most interesting thing here is the large coral reef that blocks you 
from the lagoon. It seems like the strip of land that you're standing on was 
placed here artificially, which explains why the lagoon has saltwater instead 
of fresh, and in fact how that lagoon got there in the first place."
B"on the north shore of the lagoon."
I"You can go Noth to the end of the beach, West to a small sand dune, or East 
to where a patch of reeds are growing in the sand."`
065"You are standing in the middle of a patch of reeds and other knee-high 
plants. It would be very easy to lose something around here."
B"standing in a patch of high weeds."
I"You can go West to the north shore of the lagoon, NorthWest to the edge of 
the beach, or South or East towards some odd patches of sand."`
066"The strip of land that you're now standing on was probably put here 
artificially, in order to create the lagoon." 
B"on the end of the beach."
I"You can go South to the north shore of the lagoon, or SouthEast to a patch 
of knee-high weeds."`
067"You are behind a large sand dune. A tunnel with a carved stone staircase 
leads downward into the earth."
B"behind the sand dune."
I"You can go Down the staircase, North to a peninsula, or South to the other 
side of the dune."`
068"You're treading water in the ocean below the dock, and the saltwater is 
stinging your eyes." 
B"in the ocean."
I"You can either climb Up onto the dock, or swim Down towards the bottom of 
the ocean (if you have something that would allow you to breathe while 
underwater)."`
069"As you continue to crawl through the tunnel, it occurs to you that 
although you can still see, you should have run out of light a long time ago. 
You simply dismiss it, and continue. After a few feet you notice that the 
tunnel's ceiling is getting almost high enough for you to stand up straight 
and walk. You stop moving when you see reach a point where the tunnel forks."
B"at a point where the tunnel forks."
I"One passage continues North and heads at a slightly downward tilted angle, 
another goes NorthEast to where you can see some sort of wall-painting, and 
the other passage continues to the South."`
070"You are crawling along an underground passageway that leads downward. It 
would seem that the light is provided by the room at the end of the tunnel."
B"in an underground tunnel that leads downward."
I"You can go North to the room at the end of the tunnel, or South to where 
the tunnel forks."`
071"The walls of this room themselves cast an eerie glow, perhaps from either 
a bizarre element imbedded in the rock, or some sort of phosphorous fungus. 
That eerie glow is what has been providing you with light. There is a large 
stone placed in the middle of the room."
B"in the room at the end of the tunnel."
I"The only direction that you can go is back South through the tunnel that 
led you here."`
072"The only thing in this room of any interest is the huge painting which is 
taking up most of the wall." 
B"in a tunnel, looking at a large wall painting."
I"You can either follow the tunnel that goes North, the one that goes 
SouthWest, or the one to the South that leads towards a cave-in."`
073"The tunnel is blocked by a cave-in which appears to have occurred 
recently. You can't remove the rubble left behind by the cave-in by hand, but
maybe some 'leverage' would help."
B"standing near a cave-in."
I"You can only go North towards a large wall-painting, or South (once you've 
removed the rubble left behind by the cave-in)."`
074"As you continue through the tunnel, you think you hear sounds all around 
you, but it's probably just some sort of echo."
B"in an underground tunnel."
I"You can see a dim light to the North, and a huge wallpainting to the 
South."`
075"The tunnel spreads out into an immense room here. There's a stone table 
in the middle, with a deep pit behind it. The walls themselves seem to glow 
with an un-earthly inner light."
B"in an underground room."
I"You can only head North towards a stone wall or South through a series of 
underground tunnels. Unless of course, you have some sort of death-wish and 
want to jump Down that hole."`
076"You have uncovered a tunnel that leads downward, to a large cavern. You 
slowly crawl through it, and upon reaching the end, your eyes widen and you 
feel you jaw almost hit the floor. Much to your amazement, there is a huge 
flat wooden platform ahead of you. On top of the platform is a wide 
assortment of gears and switches and levers. Behind and above the panels 
is a huge plate of glass. Astonished and amazed at finding something 
resembling a computer on an island that seemed so primal you step forward 
and pull the red handle in front of you..."
B"in the middle of a huge cavern."
I"You may only go North, and Up to the place where the cave-in took place."`
077"You are standing on a small strip of land in the middle of a wide river 
that takes in water from the ocean. After years of erosion, the river has 
eroded a small passway through the rockface."
B"in the middle of a river."
I"You can wade North towards the mouth of the river, South to a set of 'rock 
steps' that cross the river, West to the opposite bank, or East to a small 
sand dune."`
078"You edge your way along the portion of the wall that splits off to the 
north. The ground below you drops off rather rapidly. There is a pasture far 
below to the left, and to the right lies the remains of a small building."
B"on top of a high wall."
I"Since the wall is much too high on either side for you to jump down, and 
since to the north the path on top of the wall ends where a gate begins, you 
can only go back to the South."`
079"You are standing admist the ruins of an old, small building. It would 
appear that it was once an old toolshed, but simply crumbled from lack of 
upkeep."
B"standing admist the ruins of an old toolshed."
I"You may only go back North to the narrow passageway."`
080"The peninsula that you're standing on curves to the right, where a dock 
made of wood stretches out over the ocean."
B"standing on a peninsula."
I"You can go to the North where the peninsula turns right, or South to the 
back of a small sand dune."`
081"The peninsula curves to the right here, leading towards a wooden dock 
extends out over the water."
B"on a peninsula."
I"You may head East to the start of a wooden dock, or South, to the start of 
the peninsula."`
082"Where the peninsula ends, a wooden dock begins stretching out over the 
water."
B"at the start of a wooden dock."
I"You can either go East onto the dock, Down into the water, or West where 
the peninsula turns."`
083"A rope bridge starts here, spaning the deep gully far below you."
Description B:"You are at the start of a rope bridge."
I"You can travel West to cross the rope bridge, or East to the bottom of a 
huge temple that has been built into the rockface."`
084"Oops! due to a serious lack of intelligence...You are dead."
B"dead."
I" "`
085"The path that you were walking along is being blocked by a large metallic 
gate which has been built into the huge wall in front of you. It has a lock 
and heyhole that are within your reach." 
B"in front of a large gate."
I"You can go SouthWest towards a pasture, or once you find a way around that 
lock, East through the gate."`
086"At this point the wall that you have been walking on top of winds around 
into a staircase leading downward. They twist at the bottom and turn towards 
the back of a volcano."
B"at the western end of a large wall."
I"You can travel Down the staircase, or East along the top of the wall."`
087"You are standing in the middle of a large pasture. To the west, south, 
and east are walls blocking you. The pasture begins to slope downward."
B"in the middle of a pasture."
I"You can go Down the hill, NorthEast to a gate built into one of the walls, 
or climb Up onto the top of the wall behind you."`
088"You are walking down a hill in a large pasture. At the bottom of the hill 
is a path that leads to a well." 
B"on a hill, in a pasture."
I"You can either go Down to the bottom of the hill, or walk Up to the top of 
it."`
089"You are standing at the bottom of a hill in a large pasture. A path just 
East of here leads to a well."
B"at the bottom of the hill."
I"You can go East to the path that leads to a well, or walk Up the hill."`
091"You are standing on top of a small group of rocks that lead across the 
river. This river, after years of constant pressure, has eroded a small 
passway through the huge cliffs that make up most of the northern and western 
portions of the island. The river takes water in from the ocean and follows 
a winding route through the rock."
B"standing on top of a few  rocks in the middle of a river."
I"You can go North or South along the river, or East or West to either bank."`
091"You are standing on a path, just south of a water-well. Mist from the 
ocean below you blows comfortingly across your face."
B"south of a well."
I"You can go North to the well, or West to the bottom of a hill."`
092"You're walking down a narrow passageway with huge walls on either side. 
At the end of the passage is an old building lays in ruins."
B"walking down a narrow passway."
I"You can go South towards the old building, or West towards the gateway."`
093"You are standing on a set of stairs that lead into the top of a wall. 
They twist at the bottom, turning in the direction of a volcano."
B"on a staircase that leads into the top of a wall."
I"You can either go Down to where the stairs twist, or Up to where they lead 
into the top of a wall."`
094"You are in an underground tunnel, which was formed by a river that eroded 
its way through the cliffs which make up most of the western portion of the 
island. The current is pulling you away from the entrance."
B"in an underground tunnel."
I"You may go West towards the middle of the tunnel, or East towards its 
entrance."`
095"Someone has built a stone wall here, and it will have to be removed 
before you can continue."
B"standing in front of a large stone wall."
I"Unless you've removed the wall, you'll have to go back the way you came. 
Other wise, you can go North or South."`
096"As you wade along the river, you notice that the undergrowth is growing 
thicker here."
B"wading along, in a river."
I"You can go South where the river turns, or North where a set of rocks 
crosses it."`
097"At this point, the river turns sharply to the west. You can also see a 
tunnel further down to the west, where the river must go underground."
B"at a point where the river turns."
I"You can follow the river North or West."`
098"As you glance upwards at the cliffs on the north side of the river, you 
notice that they're somewhat lower than the ones on the south side. An old 
tree stump, which is on top of the northern cliff, looks like you could climb 
up to it, if only you could somehow get a rope up there."
B"You are in the river that runs through the mountains."
I"If you could get a rope up to that tree stump, you could climb Up to it. 
Otherwise, you can only follow the river to the East, ot to the West where 
the river goes underground."`
099"The river takes in its water from the sea here. The current is a bit 
stronger than before, and it pushes you backwards." 
B"at the mouth of a river."
I"Since the current is so strong, you may only go South."`
100"You are standing on a wooden dock that stretches out over the ocean. You 
glance out towards the ocean as the waves crash all around you. You can't 
help but to feel a little homesick."
B"standing on a wooden dock."
I"You may dive Down into the water, or go back to the West where the dock 
starts."`
101"The river enters an tunnel here. You can hear the echo of the water 
trickling. Otherwise, it is pitch black, and you can't see any light at the 
end. You'll need some sort of portable light source to go in there."
B"standing in a river, at the entrance to a tunnel."
I"You can only go East, unless you have a torch or a flashlight of some kind, 
in which case you can enter the tunnel to the West."`
102"The river begins to turn North here."
B"in the middle of an underground tunnel."
I"The tunnel turns both North and East here."`
103"You are standing at the southwestern point of the island, taking in the 
magnificent view. Below you the waves crash against the craggy rocks. Enough 
sight-seeing, it's time to move on."
B"at the southwestern-most point of the island."
I"You can either go NorthEast towards some hardened lawn, or SouthEast to an 
ocean viewpoint."`
104"After all of that climbing to get up here, you realize that this would be 
a perfect place to take a short rest. Apparently, someone else had the same 
idea, for there is a small campsite off to the east. In the meantime, you sit 
back and relax, taking in the view."
B"on top of a cliff"
I"You can either go East to a campsite, or Down the rope into a river."`
105"You are standing on the staircase in between a stone wall and the back of 
a small sand dune."
B"on a small set of stairs."
I"You can either go South to the stone wall, or Up to the back of a small 
sand dune."`
106"You are standing on a staircase that twists downwards. At the other end, 
it leads into the top of a wall."
B"on a twisting staircase."
I"You can either go Up the staircase, North to a small overlook that reaches 
out over a deep pit, or East towards the back of a volcano."`
107"In front of you stands a rather large well, with a crank on one end, and 
a rope with a bucket on the other. The bucket is now at the bottom of the 
well. You can hear water flowing at the bottom, and you can smell the ocean."
B"in front of a well."
I"You can go North to one end of a rope bridge, South to a path that leads to 
a large hill, or Down the rope that the bucket hangs on, if you had some way 
to see once you got down there."`
108"You are leaning over the edge of a small overpass that extends over a 
deep pit. You try squinting a bit, but you still can not see the bottom. You
pick up a small rock, and drop it into the pit. You wait a few moments, but 
don't hear it hit the bottom."
B"an a small overpass."
I"Unless you really want to find out what's at the bottom of the pit, you can 
only go South."`
109"You are standing on the bank of a river, behind a large cliff. This bank 
of the river leads upward somehow, in an eastern direction." 
B"on the opposite bank of a river."
I"You can either go West up the hill, or East and across the river."`
110"The tunnel turns again, this time east and south. The waterlevel seems to 
have lowered. You can see light to the east, where there must be a hole in 
the ceiling of the tunnel."
B"in an underground river."
I"You can go East towards the light, or South towards the middle of the 
tunnel."`
111"You are now standing on the northern side of a large volcano that takes 
up the majority of the southwestern portion of the island."
B"behind volcano."
I"You can either go Up to the top of the volcano, or East towards a set of 
winding stairs."`
112"You are treading water next to a short wooden dock."
B"treading water."
I"You can only go Up onto the dock, unless you have some means of breathing 
while underwater, you can't go Down."`
113"You are swimming along the bottom of the ocean, looking for anything 
interesting or out of the ordinary." 
B"at the bottom of the ocean."
I"You can only swim Upward, to the top of the water."`
114"The level of the water in the tunnel has dropped down to only five or six 
inches. A large hole under the water running through the tunnel, it looks 
just about big enough for you to fit through."
B"in a river, underground."
I"Unless you have some way of breathing while underwater, you can't go Down 
through the hole, and therefore will have to go West towards the light, and 
through the tunnel."`
115"You now standing knee-deep in an underground river. Above you is a large 
round 'tunnel' going straight up. At first you're confused, but after 
noticing the rope and bucket, you realise that its just a normal water-well. 
The bucket is now down, and the rope looks thick enough to climb up. You 
suddenly realize that the water is saltwater and you have to wonder why 
someone would want to build a well here."
B"below a well."
I"Since the bucket (and rope) is down, you can climb Up to the top of the 
well. You also can follow the tunnel to the East or West."`
116"In front of you is one end of a rope bridge that spans a deep gulley far 
below you."
B"at one end of a rope bridge."
I"You may go West to the northwestern point of the island, South to a well, 
or East across the rope bridge."`
117"You are now standing on the northwestern point of the island. There is a 
series of short ledges that are not totally unsimular to a gigantic 
staircase."
B"at the top of huge set of short ledges."
I"You may climb Down to the first ledge, or go East to the start of a rope 
bridge."`
118"You are resting inside a naturally-formed dugout, probably shaped and 
molded by the lava the last time the volcano erupted. The dugout resemble a 
very small cave, about seven feet deep into the volcano, six feet high, and 
six feet wide. Its deep enough to block out the sun, and wide enough to let 
in the refreshing sea breeze."
B"in a dugout."
I"You can go Up to the top of the volcano, Down to a pathway that leads up 
the volcano, East to a deadend, or West into the middle of a patch of 
boiling-hot lava."`
119"You are now walking across a rickety old bridge. Below you is a deep 
gulley with the ocean's waves crashing at the bottom."
B"in the middle of a rope bridge."
I"The bridge goes East and West"`
120"The top level of this tunnel seems to be covered with some kind of mirror 
that shines incredibly bright white light all around you, almost blinding you. 
You try squinting, but it is no use, the light is simply too bright."
B"at the top of a temple."
I"You may only go back Down the steps to the base of the temple."`
121"While standing on the small ledge inside the volcano, you have to keep 
yourself from looking towards the lava, because the heat that it casts 
against your face is virtually unbearable. You had best be moving on soon."
B"on a small ledge, inside a volcano."
I"You may only climp back Up the rope."`
122"You now stand on the top of a volcano, peering down at the lava flowing 
deep within it. To your right, sticking out of the ground, is a small metal 
rod. Also, not too far below it is what looks like a small ledge."
B"on top of a volcano."
I"If you could find some way to get Down to that ledge, you might be able to 
see if there's anything there of interest. Otherwise, you can go down the 
North or South sides of the volcano."`
123"After this ledge the other start becoming much larger, making it 
impossible to go any lower."
B"on a huge ledge."
I"You can only climb back Up to the top of the huge stairs."`
124"A large boulder blocks your path in this direction, so you'll have to go 
back."
B"at a dead end."
I"You may only go back West"`
125"You now stand before a huge cave entrance that leads underground. You 
hear some sort of mechanism shirring and clicking deep below the earth. You 
sigh, take a deep breathe, and step forward. You've come a long way, and 
there's no turning back now."
B" "
I"This concludes the first session of The Cycon Oddyssey. You have overcome 
many obstacles and mental challanges. I regret that you had to come so far, 
and you still don't know where you are, how you go here, why you were brought 
here, or even what the name means. You don't even know where 'here' is. If 
you enjoyed this game (or even if you didn't) look for The Cycon Odyssey II, 
'Tracing Roots', possibly coming soon to a Hard Drive near you."`[
